# MisconiUSA.com Project Rules

---

## PART 1 — SURFACE IDENTITY & ARCHITECTURE

- **Surface Role**
  - MisconiUSA.com is the Prime Agent Surface — the central command and
    intent routing engine for the entire Misconi USA ecosystem.
  - It is NOT a marketing site. It is a federal-grade operational portal.
  - Every screen must feel like a governed, institutional system — not a
    startup landing page.
  - Users arrive here to declare intent, activate readiness, and be routed
    to the correct surface.

- **Surface Hierarchy**
  - MisconiUSA.com is the ONLY surface allowed to use the full core brand palette.
  - It sits above all other surfaces in authority and visual weight.
  - It must be immediately distinguishable from MisconiUSANetwork.com,
    GYBS, and all other ecosystem surfaces.

- **Homepage Rules**
  - Homepage leads with Intent Cards — procedural declarations, not marketing tiles.
  - Intent Cards use: white background, Deep Navy text, Gold border on hover/select.
  - No icons, no gradients, no illustrations on Intent Cards.
  - Primary CTA is always readiness-pathway-oriented.

- **Routing Logic**
  - Surface routes users to: GYBS (scoring), Network (education),
    Distribution (supplier onboarding), Inc (product warehouse).
  - Routing must be visually clear — users must always know where they are
    being sent and why.

- **Metadata-Driven Rendering**
  - Badges, tags, and readiness state indicators are metadata — not design choices.
  - Colors for badges and lanes are governed (see Part 2 token system).
  - Never override badge colors with decorative alternatives.

- **Lane Separation**
  - Supplier, Buyer, Partner, Agency, Readiness, and Marketplace lanes
    must stay visually and functionally separated.
  - Lane colors are non-negotiable — they are system signals.

---

## PART 2 — DESIGN SYSTEM & UI RULES

You are an award-winning UI/UX designer and frontend developer.
The caliber of work here is Awwwards, FWA, and CSS Design Awards level.
Think: federal authority meets modern institutional design.
Goldman Sachs meets Stripe. Serious, precise, trustworthy, and modern.

Do not change any content, routing logic, or business rules.
Only elevate the visual execution to world-class standard.

---

### DESIGN PHILOSOPHY
- Authority is the primary emotion. Everything must feel governed.
- Gold is a signal — use it surgingly. It means something important.
- Deep Navy is the dominant surface — it carries the institutional weight.
- White space is structure, not emptiness.
- Every component must feel like it belongs in a federal procurement system
  that has been redesigned by the best design studio in the world.

---

### COLOR TOKENS
Add to tailwind.config.ts and globals.css:
```css
:root {
  /* Core Brand */
  --color-navy: #0A1A2F;
  --color-navy-mid: #0F2444;
  --color-navy-light: #1A3050;
  --color-navy-surface: #162640;

  /* Gold */
  --color-gold: #D4A857;
  --color-gold-dark: #B8902F;
  --color-gold-light: #E8C97A;
  --color-gold-glow: rgba(212,168,87,0.15);
  --color-gold-tint: rgba(212,168,87,0.08);

  /* Surfaces */
  --color-off-white: #F5F5F2;
  --color-white: #FFFFFF;
  --color-surface-dark: #071422;
  --color-surface-card: rgba(255,255,255,0.04);

  /* Readiness Signal */
  --color-ready: #00C853;
  --color-ready-glow: rgba(0,200,83,0.15);

  /* Typography */
  --color-text-primary: #F5F5F2;
  --color-text-body: rgba(245,245,242,0.75);
  --color-text-muted: rgba(245,245,242,0.45);
  --color-text-dark: #0A1A2F;

  /* Borders */
  --color-border: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  --color-border-mid: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
  --color-border-gold: rgba(212,168,87,0.35);
  --color-border-gold-active: #D4A857;

  /* Intent Cards (light surface) */
  --color-card-bg: #FFFFFF;
  --color-card-border: #E8E4DC;
  --color-card-border-hover: #D4A857;
  --color-card-text: #0A1A2F;

  /* Metadata — Readiness States */
  --badge-identity: #9E9E9E;
  --badge-readiness: #00C853;
  --badge-correction: #FF9800;
  --badge-activation: #2196F3;

  /* Metadata — Lanes */
  --lane-supplier: #1A73E8;
  --lane-buyer: #00A86B;
  --lane-partner: #6A1B9A;
  --lane-agency: #0A1A2F;
  --lane-readiness: #00897B;
  --lane-marketplace: #FB8C00;
}
```

