## UPDATED GLOBAL UI RULES

- Deep Navy is dominant — lean into it, do not fight it
- Gold is a signal — every single use must be earned and intentional
- No light backgrounds on more than 2 consecutive sections
- No stock photography — dashboard mockups and system UI only
- No rounded blobs, gradients on buttons, or startup-style illustrations
- Every section needs: label + H2 + supporting text + content + optional CTA
- Every card needs: hover state, active state, and focus state
- Every button needs: hover, active, focus, loading, and disabled states
- All form inputs need: default, hover, focus, error, and success states
- Shadows on dark surfaces: rgba(0,0,0,0.40) minimum — deep, not soft
- Shadows on light surfaces: rgba(0,0,0,0.08) maximum — subtle
- All text on dark backgrounds passes 4.5:1 contrast minimum
- All interactive elements are keyboard navigable
- ARIA labels on all form elements, buttons, and icons
- Lazy load all images and mockup assets
- No lorem ipsum — every element uses real content

